Company Description                    




                        Sri Lanka Telecom PLC provides telecommunication services in Sri Lanka. The customers include multinational corporations, large and small corporate, retail, and domestic customers in Sri Lanka and internationally. The service includes domestic and international fixed and mobile telephone. The company also provides Internet services, data services, domestic and international leased circuits, broadband, satellite uplink, maritime transmission, Internet protocol television service, directory publishing, and Wi-max services. In addition, Sri Lanka Telecom PLC offers voice, data, and video, integrated services digital network, domestic and international operator assisted services, voice mail, direct inward dialing, digital subscriber lines, and virtual private network services. Furthermore, the company provides SLTPLUS services, which offer international direct dialing, call forwarding, call waiting, conference calling, abbreviated dialing, hot line, and absentee services. Additionally, the company offers IP transit services and manpower solutions. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Colombo, Sri Lanka.                    


